erior</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/31/01 6:12:08 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ac.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Hmmm</span><hr size=1> I think the major argument (and I agree here, even being a human and all) is that although the current racial advantages by all other than Ogres can usually be met and exceeded by most warriors INCLUDING that race.  Here are some examples.<br>
<br>
Troll:  They get regen.  There are regen items, but Trolls can use them too, so they will still have higher regen toe to toe with, say, a human.<br>
<br>
Iksar:  They get the AC bonus.  You can buff up and get some really good AC items.  But so can Iksars.<br>
<br>
Elves:  They get forage.  Not really a big racial advantage, honestly.  But you can bum summoned food or be a baker.  So can elves.<br>
<br>
Ogres:  No frontal Stun.  Currently there is no item or spell that can recreate this effect.  If this is given (quested, spell, whatever), what do Ogres get to continue with this trend?<br>
<br>
I know I didn't list all the races, but you get the idea of why Ogres are upset about this.  For all the current racial advantages that REALLY are advantages (not forage, hide, sneak, infravision - these are mostly perks) there usually is some way to duplicate the effect to a point, but those races that already have the advantage can also use that &quot;buff.&quot;<br>
<br>
The lack of stun from all sides is an interesting proposal, but there doesn't seem to be much usefulness in it.  If an Ogre isn't getting stunned normally, they probably aren't going to turn their back on the mob anyway.<br>
<br>
I know I'm adding to the fire here, but I wanted to point out why this has gone on for so many posts as is.<br>
<br>
I'm only 47, but I've been stunned enough to absolutely hate it as is.  I can't even imagine how horrible it would be end game.  But I do also see why Ogres are so upset about this, as it is a unique ability that has serious advantages as is.<br>
<br>
Chaotic Conformity<br>
47th Level Warrior<br>
Bristlebane Server<br>
<br>
P.S.  Please keep the discussion courteous, consice, and most of all constructive.  It does no good to flame each other, call each other fatasses and midgets, or other such nonsense.  Maybe we can all work to a positive agreement and the entire class will benefit rather than squabling over differences.  Thanks! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ujorplee.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jorp Lee</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/1/01 7:13:17 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ac.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Hmmm</span><hr size=1> too bad smolder sucks ;p <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukagmoo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kagmoo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/2/01 12:32:14 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ac.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Hmmm</span><hr size=1> Just a suggestion I liked the Idea of another 60th level discipline that gives unstunablility from the front.  This could could be on a 10 min timer and last 3 min but would allow Ogres to use defensive and be a better tank in certain situations with out being the &quot;only tank&quot;.  This is a compromise that gives the other races what they want while still providing a bonus to the ogres.  Sure so other warriors get an extra discipline but it only mimics what ogres already have allowing them to use Defensive.<br>
<br>
No I am not Uber but doesnt this address the issue in a compromising way.  If I am wrong then please take me to school because I do pay attention. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usikk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sikk</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/5/01 6:47:30 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ac.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Hmmm</span><hr size=1> Kag,<br>
<br>
Giving other warriors a /disc at 60 that takes frontal stuns away does nothing. The mobs people are talking about in this thread NEED the 55 Defensive disc to be tanked. Frontal stuns hurt your ability to control aggro. Thats what all this is about.<br>
<br>
I think its appropriate to give it to everyone. Even if its only in the form of adding it to Defensive. Lets face it, how many guilds have 5 or more Ogre Wars +55? Not that many. Why not open a few more possibilities up for the smaller guilds who aren't powergamers? At the end of the day the only people hurt in any way are the few uber Ogres who are even in a position to tank these things. And even they are at an advantage because the guild will have more success more often even if they are not there to help. By this I meen a Troll, Iksar etc can fill in and do the job as well as an ogre when it's needed.<br>
<br>
Either side of this arguement has selfish reasons for wanting these changes to be made or not made. But the reality is there are tons more normal warriors then Ogres.<br>
<br>
Give all wars no stuns during Defensive and lets get on with having fun. <p><img 
